---
---

<section class="py-24 md:py-36 bg-warm-cream">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-storehouse-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase reveal">
        The conversation
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-text-deep leading-[1.05] reveal reveal-delay-1">
        Bob said something nobody else was saying.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-16">

      <!-- Prose column -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-7 space-y-6 text-lg text-text-body leading-relaxed reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <p>
          Most agents ask what you're looking for in a house. Bob asked
          what kind of life I wanted.
        </p>
        <p>
          Before showing me a single listing, he sat me down with a calculator.
        </p>
        <p class="font-quote italic text-text-deep">
          &ldquo;You're approved for $250,000,&rdquo; he said.
          &ldquo;But I don't think you should spend it.&rdquo;
        </p>
        <p>
          He showed me the real cost difference between buying a $250,000
          home and a $127,000 one &mdash; the monthly payments, the interest
          over 30 years, and what that extra money could become if I invested
          it instead. The numbers were staggering. The difference wasn't just
          a bigger house &mdash; it was decades of compounding working against
          me instead of for me.
        </p>
        <p class="font-quote italic text-text-deep">
          &ldquo;I'm not going to tell you which house to buy. But I want
          you to see the value of leaving yourself some margin.&rdquo;
        </p>
        <p>
          <span class="font-semibold text-text-deep">Margin.</span> The word
          stuck with me.
        </p>
        <p>
          I bought the modest starter home. And for the first time, I had room
          to breathe.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Quotes column -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-5 space-y-8">

        <!-- First Bob quote -->
        <div class="relative reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="bg-warm-white rounded-2xl p-8 border-l-4 border-l-storehouse-500 border border-storehouse-100/40">
            <span class="block font-quote text-5xl text-storehouse-400/30 leading-none select-none -mb-2" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</span>
            <p class="font-quote text-xl sm:text-2xl text-text-deep italic leading-snug">
              You're approved for $250,000. But I don't think you should spend it.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-8 h-px bg-storehouse-300"></div>
              <p class="text-sm text-text-muted font-medium">Bob</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Second Bob quote -->
        <div class="relative reveal reveal-delay-3">
          <div class="bg-warm-white rounded-2xl p-8 border-l-4 border-l-gold-500 border border-storehouse-100/40">
            <span class="block font-quote text-5xl text-gold-400/40 leading-none select-none -mb-2" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</span>
            <p class="font-quote text-xl sm:text-2xl text-text-deep italic leading-snug">
              I'm not going to tell you which house to buy. But I want you to see
              the value of leaving yourself some margin.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-8 h-px bg-gold-400"></div>
              <p class="text-sm text-text-muted font-medium">Bob</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>
